g.text: UML Diagram: Class ConceptSystem in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.
- The arrows of the inheritance tree are

a.title: ― Concept: Unit of thought differentiated by characteristics (from the Generic Statistical Information Model version 1.2: https://statswiki.unece.org/display/clickablegsim/Concept).
a.xlink:title: ― Concept: Unit of thought differentiated by characteristics (from the Generic Statistical Information Model version 1.2: https://statswiki.unece.org/display/clickablegsim/Concept).

a.title: ― ConceptSystemCorrespondence: Relationship between 2 or more concept systems described through mapping similarity relationships between their member concepts.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptSystemCorrespondence: Relationship between 2 or more concept systems described through mapping similarity relationships between their member concepts.

a.title: ― ConceptualDomain: Set of concepts, where each concept is intended to be used as the meaning (signified) for a datum.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptualDomain: Set of concepts, where each concept is intended to be used as the meaning (signified) for a datum.

a.title: ― ConceptStructure: Relations of concepts within a collection.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptStructure: Relations of concepts within a collection.

a.title: ― Collection: Generic container that supports different types of groupings, from unordered sets to all sorts of hierarchies, nesting and ordered sets/bags.
a.xlink:title: ― Collection: Generic container that supports different types of groupings, from unordered sets to all sorts of hierarchies, nesting and ordered sets/bags.

a.title: ― CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.
a.xlink:title: ― CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.

a.title: ― Reference: Provides a way of pointing to resources outside of the information described in the set of DDI-CDI metadata.
a.xlink:title: ― Reference: Provides a way of pointing to resources outside of the information described in the set of DDI-CDI metadata.

a.title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.
a.xlink:title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.

a.title: ― ObjectName: A standard means of expressing a name for a class object. A linguistic signifier. Human understandable name (word, phrase, or mnemonic) that reflects the ISO/IEC 11179-5 naming principles.
a.xlink:title: ― ObjectName: A standard means of expressing a name for a class object. A linguistic signifier. Human understandable name (word, phrase, or mnemonic) that reflects the ISO/IEC 11179-5 naming principles.

a.title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...
a.xlink:title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...

a.title: ― CategorySet: Concept system where the underlying concepts are categories.
a.xlink:title: ― CategorySet: Concept system where the underlying concepts are categories.

a.title: ― structures: Concept structure structures concept system.
a.xlink:title: ― structures: Concept structure structures concept system.

a.title: ― has: Concept system has zero to many concepts.
a.xlink:title: ― has: Concept system has zero to many concepts.

a.title: ― isDefinedBy: Concept system is defined by zero to many concepts. The conceptual basis for the collection of members.
a.xlink:title: ― isDefinedBy: Concept system is defined by zero to many concepts. The conceptual basis for the collection of members.

a.title: ― maps: Concept system correspondence maps two to many concept systems. Realization of structures in symmetric relation. When concepts of a single concept system are mapped, the Concept has to appear twice as target.
a.xlink:title: ― maps: Concept system correspondence maps two to many concept systems. Realization of structures in symmetric relation. When concepts of a single concept system are mapped, the Concept has to appear twice as target.

a.title: ― takesConceptsFrom: Conceptual domain takes concept from zero to one concept system.
a.xlink:title: ― takesConceptsFrom: Conceptual domain takes concept from zero to one concept system.
